==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Beshrew
<hw>Be*shrew"</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To curse; to
execrate.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Beshrew</qex> me, but I love her heartily.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ Often a very mild form of imprecation; sometimes so far
from implying a curse, as to be uttered coaxingly, nay even with some
tenderness. <rj><au>Schmidt.</au></rj> </note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Beshroud</ent>⟦br⟧
